headline.main: No Criminal Charges in California Balcony Collapse That Killed Irish Students
headline.print_headline: No Criminal Charges in California Balcony Collapse That Killed Irish Students

docs.snippet: No criminal charges will be filed in connection with the deadly collapse of an apartment balcony in Berkeley, California, last year in which five visiting Irish students and an American friend were killed, prosecutors said on Tuesday....
docs.lead_paragraph: No criminal charges will be filed in connection with the deadly collapse of an apartment balcony in Berkeley, California, last year in which five visiting Irish students and an American friend were killed, prosecutors said on Tuesday.

headline.main: Wells Fargo to Pay $8.5 Million for California Privacy Violations
headline.print_headline: Wells Fargo to Pay $8.5 Million for California Privacy Violations

docs.snippet: A Wells Fargo & Co unit will pay $8.5 million to California and five of the state's counties to settle charges that it violated customers' privacy by recording their calls without first notifying them, state prosecutors said on Tuesday....
